00:23:00,166 --> 00:23:02,333
- Daphne told me before
that the Great Rabbit

518
00:23:02,416 --> 00:23:05,500
is always drawn
to large amounts of mana.

519
00:23:05,583 --> 00:23:08,666
Roswaal, I'm calling
a truce for now,

520
00:23:08,750 --> 00:23:11,000
'cause our focus should be
on getting everybody outside.

521
00:23:11,083 --> 00:23:12,958
["Memento" playing in Japanese]

522
00:23:13,041 --> 00:23:15,458
- How would we do that?

523
00:23:15,541 --> 00:23:17,166
Until the trial is completed,

524
00:23:17,250 --> 00:23:19,208
those in the Sanctuary
cannot leave the barrier.

525
00:23:19,291 --> 00:23:22,416
- Hang on! I'm not finished yet!

526
00:23:22,500 --> 00:23:24,625
You might think
it can wait until next time,

527
00:23:24,708 --> 00:23:25,791
but I'm telling you...

528
00:23:25,875 --> 00:23:27,125
- You seem to be mistaken

529
00:23:27,208 --> 00:23:30,333
about one important factor,
Subaru.

530
00:23:30,416 --> 00:23:31,041
While you may well
have the ability

531
00:23:31,125 --> 00:23:34,083
to start over, I do not.

532
00:23:34,166 --> 00:23:35,958
- [grunts]

533
00:23:36,041 --> 00:23:38,000
- My present self will end here.

534
00:23:38,083 --> 00:23:38,791
It's sudden,

535
00:23:38,875 --> 00:23:41,083
but that's quite all right.

536
00:23:41,166 --> 00:23:41,875
Another version of me
will be there

537
00:23:41,958 --> 00:23:42,875
after your return

538
00:23:42,958 --> 00:23:44,833
to the beginning.

539
00:23:44,916 --> 00:23:46,791
As long as he fulfills my goals

540
00:23:46,875 --> 00:23:48,625
one day, it makes no difference.

541
00:23:50,583 --> 00:23:51,750
- But that isn't how

542
00:23:51,833 --> 00:23:53,250
any normal human thinks.

543
00:23:54,666 --> 00:23:56,666
- There's not
a single doubt in my mind

544
00:23:56,750 --> 00:23:59,458
that the time will come
when you truly catch up to me.

545
00:23:59,541 --> 00:24:00,083
Now listen carefully.

546
00:24:00,166 --> 00:24:01,166
There is only one thing

547
00:24:01,250 --> 00:24:03,500
that is clearly and above all

548
00:24:03,583 --> 00:24:06,083
the most precious to you
in this whole world.

549
00:24:06,166 --> 00:24:08,583
You have to get rid
of everything else but that

550
00:24:08,666 --> 00:24:09,541
and think of nothing
but making sure

551
00:24:09,625 --> 00:24:11,666
what you hold so dearly
is protected.

552
00:24:11,750 --> 00:24:13,875
- [gasps]

553
00:24:13,958 --> 00:24:15,833
- By doing that...

554
00:24:15,916 --> 00:24:17,500
- [chitters]

555
00:24:17,583 --> 00:24:19,625
- [chittering]

556
00:24:20,125 --> 00:24:21,916
- Roswaal! No!

557
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:24,083
- you can then...

558
00:24:24,166 --> 00:24:26,125
become just like yours truly.

559
00:24:26,208 --> 00:24:27,208
[groans]

560
00:24:34,791 --> 00:24:35,541
[song ends]

561
00:24:38,041 --> 00:24:39,916
- [groaning]
- [footsteps shuffling]

562
00:24:46,958 --> 00:24:47,916
EMILIA: Subaru?

563
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:50,833
Subaru, it is you!

564
00:24:50,916 --> 00:24:53,250
- [giggles]
- [music box playing]

565
00:24:53,333 --> 00:24:57,125
Oh, my goodness.
Where have you been?

566
00:24:57,208 --> 00:25:00,791
I was getting
so worried about you.

567
00:25:00,875 --> 00:25:02,541
Are you all right? Exhausted?

568
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:05,041
[giggles]

569
00:25:05,125 --> 00:25:07,500
Okay, I see then.

570
00:25:07,583 --> 00:25:08,833
That's good to hear.

571
00:25:11,125 --> 00:25:13,500
Hey, Subaru!

572
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:19,291
Come here! You like resting
your head on my lap, don't
you?

573
00:25:23,625 --> 00:25:25,208
Aww. Are you sleepy?

574
00:25:25,291 --> 00:25:26,708
- [groans]

575
00:25:30,125 --> 00:25:32,291
[music skipping]

576
00:25:37,166 --> 00:25:39,333
- Don't force it, okay?

577
00:25:39,416 --> 00:25:41,500
You always end up
pushing yourself too hard

578
00:25:41,583 --> 00:25:43,791
for the sake of other people.

579
00:25:45,125 --> 00:25:46,166
It gives me mixed feelings.

580
00:25:46,250 --> 00:25:48,791
If I'm being honest,

581
00:25:48,875 --> 00:25:51,041
I only want you
to do that for me,

582
00:25:51,125 --> 00:25:52,833
although I wouldn't
like a Subaru

583
00:25:52,916 --> 00:25:53,791
who never looked
at anybody else.

584
00:25:53,875 --> 00:25:56,166
Sorry.

585
00:25:56,250 --> 00:25:58,041
I'm pretty selfish, aren't I?

586
00:25:58,125 --> 00:25:59,666
- [groans]

587
00:25:59,750 --> 00:26:01,208
- Huh?

588
00:26:01,291 --> 00:26:02,291
[giggles]

